# Jira MCP Fast Path

Use this default flow for Jira requests to minimize repeated searching.

## Default context

- Jira site: `your-company.atlassian.net`
- Cloud ID: `<YOUR_CLOUD_ID>`
- Default project suggestion for integrations work: `<YOUR_PROJECT_KEY>` (confirm if user asks to create)

## Tool path policy

- Do not run broad tool discovery for Atlassian MCP on every Jira request.
- Use the known tool descriptor path directly: `<YOUR_MCP_TOOLS_PATH>` (e.g. `~/.cursor/projects/.../mcps/plugin-atlassian-atlassian/tools/`).
- Read only the specific tool schema needed before each call (required).
- If a call fails due to auth or schema mismatch, then run discovery as fallback.

## Jira execution defaults

- For read-only Jira requests, use direct MCP calls after reading the relevant schema.
- For creation/update requests, confirm intent and key metadata first:
  - project key
  - issue type
  - summary
  - parent/epic if applicable
- Keep ticket content PM-level: define required behavior and acceptance criteria, avoid implementation details.
- Story template usage:
  - Use the PM story template by default only when no different content has been discussed and agreed.
  - If custom content is discussed and agreed, that agreed content overrides the template.
  - Do not force bug/task/support-issue tickets to follow the story template.
